cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.CR

The paper deals with click-through rate (CTR) prediction for online search advertising systems, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.IR and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also utilizes deep learning techniques for text and image representation, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed approach in terms of online performance, which relates to computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-category.
